[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in court charged with rape after Cardiff sex attack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 40-year-old man has appeared in court charged with rape following an alleged sexual assault in Cardiff city centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Remus Hamza, from Riverside, has been charged in relation to an incident on 20 September at Cardiff Civic Centre.
He appeared at Cardiff Magistrates' Court on Saturday where he confirmed his name and date of birth.
He will appear at Cardiff Crown Court on 12 October.
